"Lemonade is a sweetened lemon-flavored beverage.\nThere are varieties of lemonade found throughout the world. In North America and South Asia, cloudy lemonade dominates. It is traditionally a homemade drink using lemon juice, water, and a sweetener such as cane sugar, simple syrup or honey. In the United Kingdom and Australia, clear lemonade, a carbonated drink, is more common. Despite the differences between the drinks, each is known simply as \"lemonade\" in countries where it is dominant.The suffix \"-ade\" may also be applied to other similar drinks made with different fruits, such as limeade, orangeade, or cherryade."